15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1911 of Title 25, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The State of Oklahoma hereby adopts the non-legally binding
20 Working Definition of Anti-Semitism adopted by the International
21 Holocaust Remembrance Alliance (IHRA) on May 26, 2016, including the
22 contemporary examples of anti-Semitism set forth therein,
23 exclusively as a tool and guide for training, education, and
